'''''Islams and Modernities''''' is a book by [[Aziz al-Azmeh]], a professor at [[Central European University]] in [[Budapest]], [[Hungary]].{{citation needed|date=February 2017}} It was released on [https://people.ceu.edu/sites/people.ceu.hu/files/profile/attachment/1724/aafullpublicationslist.pdf 1993].<ref name="Islams_Modernities"/> The book explore the history of interaction between [[Islam]] and [[Europe]], analyzing myths about those interactions created by [[Orientalism|Orientalist]] and [[Islamist]] viewpoints.<ref>{{Citation | last =al-Azmeh | first =Aziz | author-link =Aziz al-Azmeh | title =Islams and Modernities | place = | publisher =[[Verso Books]] | date = October 17, 1996 | month= | language =English | isbn = 9781859841068 }}</ref> A new version was released on August 7, 2009, also examining "the discourse surrounding Islamism and irrationalism after 9/11."<ref name="PenguinRandomHouse_Islams"/>
==Reception==
''[[The Guardian]]'' wrote that "''Islams and Modernities'' raises urgent questions that are central to the concerns of the contemporary world.”<ref name="PenguinRandomHouse_Islams">{{cite web|title=Penguin Random House|url=http://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/books/232558/islams-and-modernities-by-aziz-al-azmeh/9781844673858/}}</ref> '' [[New Statesman]]'' wrote that “Aziz Al-Azmeh is perhaps the most original thinker on these themes in Britain today."<ref name="PenguinRandomHouse_Islams"/>
