The '''Medawar Lecture''' was an annual lecture on the [[philosophy of science]] organised by the [[Royal Society of London]] in memory of Sir [[Peter Medawar]]. It was last delivered in 2004 after which it was merged with the [[Wilkins Lecture]] and the [[Bernal Lecture]] to form the [[Wilkins-Bernal-Medawar Lecture]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://royalsociety.org/Wilkins-Bernal-Medawar-Lecture/| title = The 2010 Wilkins-Bernal-Medawar Lecture|publisher=The Royal Society|accessdate = 14 August 2010}}</ref>
