{{Infobox University |image_name = |image_size = 200px |name = Social Science Research Laboratory (SSRL) |motto = |established = 1974 |director= |campus = [[San Diego State University]] |city = [[San Diego, California|San Diego]] |state = [[California]] |country = [[United States|USA]] |website= [http://ssrl.sdsu.edu ssrl.sdsu.edu] }}
The '''Social Science Research Laboratory (SSRL)''' is a component of the [[San Diego State University College of Arts & Letters|College of Arts & Letters]] at [[San Diego State University|San Diego State University (SDSU)]] in [[San Diego, California]].
==Functions== The SSRL provide comprehensive [[survey research]] and program evaluation services to [[university]] faculty, administration, students, and regional [[government]] and [[non-profit organizations]], and to provide education and training in current survey research and program evaluation methods to SDSU students. The SSRL also provides information on current best practices in survey research [[methodology]] and program evaluation to SDSU students, faculty, staff, and the greater [[Southern California|San Diego community]]. ===Standards=== Activities are conducted in accordance with the [[American Association for Public Opinion Research|American Association for Public Opinion Research (AAPOR)]] Code of Professional Ethics and Practices. ===Affiliations=== * AAPOR: All of SSRL’s full-time staff are members of the [[AAPOR]]. * AEA: The SSRL staff specialize in [[Evaluation|evaluation research]], and are members of the [http://www.eval.org/ American Evaluation Association (AEA)]. * CMOR: The SSRL is a member of the [https://web.archive.org/web/20081029210301/http://www.cmor.org/ Council on Marketing and Opinion Research (CMOR)]. * EMPAQ: The SSRL is a certified independent data collection contractor for [http://www.empaq.org/ Employer Measures of Production, Absence, and Quality (EMPAQ)].
